🎄 Garden Glow at @mobotgarden 🎄

If you haven’t been to see the lights at Missouri Botanical Garden yet, bundle up and get tickets now! It runs through January 7 and is such a fun date night or family outing. They’ve got plenty of interactive photo ops along the route, food and drink options including s’mores over a bonfire, and all the festive music and lights to enjoy.

Pro tip: parking can be a little chaotic if it’s a busy night. There are a few restaurants within walking distance to the garden entrance - park there and walk for an easy in and out, plus a great meal before or after your garden experience!

Let’s make Blood Orange Sangria!

Did you know @dierbergs features 25 great wines under $30!? They have so many wines to choose from and many of them have personalized notes from Greg Dierberg about why he loves the wine and how you can use it.

I love making sangria because it is SO versatile! You can choose any base wine you want, your favorite fruit to soak in it, and whatever alcohol, juice, or soda to add more flavor. Here’s my go-to recipe for a red wine sangria.

Ingredients:
• One bottle red wine
• 1 cup orange juice
• 1/2 cup brandy 
• 1/4 cup coconut sugar
• 2 blood oranges, sliced
• 1 package frozen berries
• 2 cans Blood Orange Tangerine Spindrift

Directions:
Mix everything together and enjoy! I like to use frozen fruit to keep the sangria cold without watering it down with ice. I also like to make this a day in advance of when I need to serve it so that everything has time to soak and meld together.

Marinated Cucumbers ✨🥒

Every time I post on my stories when I make these I get some questions about how I cut the cucumbers and the recipe I use! Here’s a brief tutorial to help you make them at home using Persian cucumbers - I only learned this by watching several videos I found from Googling it :)

1. Lay the cucumber on one side in between two chopsticks or skewers.
2. Slice perpendicular across the cucumber in about half-inch segments (the chopsticks should prevent you from slicing all the way through.
3. Flip the cucumber over to the other side, keeping it between the chopsticks.
4. Slice across the cucumber at a 45-degree angle on this side, still in roughly half-inch segments.
5. Salt the cucumbers to remove moisture for about 20 minutes and be sure to wash the salt off.
6. Pour your marinade over the cucumbers.
7. Either enjoy now or let them sit in a container in the fridge to soak up even more flavor!

I eyeball the marinade like I said in the video, but here is approximately what I use:
• 3 tablespoons rice vinegar
• 1 tablespoon sesame oil
• 1 tablespoon coconut aminos or soy sauce
• 1 tablespoon honey (more or less depending on how sweet you want it)
• 1 teaspoon minced garlic
• Pinch of salt and pepper
• I didn’t have any when I made this video but is usually add some crushed red pepper flakes for a touch of spice as well

Enjoy and let me know if you make these!!!

Chickpea Oatmeal!?

I am always looking for healthy new breakfast ideas and was skeptical about this at first but I’m SO glad I tried @buychichi! ChiChi (named for a combination of CHIckpea and founder CHIara’s name) is a new local company that was recently developed and launched by WashU students.

I’m here to tell you, this was really freaking good! They currently have three flavors - Peanut Butter Banana, Apple Almond Cinnamon, and Dark Chocolate Blueberry (the one featured in the video). Chickpeas are a better breakfast option because they are higher in protein, higher in fiber, and lower in carbs than oats. The texture is slightly different but still has the slight chew of oats and it wasn’t too mushy or watery. And it’s convenient as it comes together with just a little liquid (milk or water) and 90 seconds in the microwave!

I love an innovative and healthy idea like this, so if that’s something you’re looking for be sure to give @buychichi a follow and place an order soon!!

ELOTE DIP for National Chip & Dip Day! 🌽

I love that @dierbergs carries @rosalitascantina house-made tortilla chips and dips! I’m sharing my easy recipe for Elote Dip below that you can serve alongside your favorite chips.

Ingredients:
• 3 cups frozen corn
• 1/2 cup mayonnaise
• 1/2 cup crema (Mexican sour cream)
• 1/2 cup grated cotija cheese
• Tajin seasoning to taste (I use about 2 tablespoons)
• Juice of one lime

Instructions:
1. Roast the corn on the stove, if desired. You can also just use frozen corn straight from the bag.
2. Mix together all of the ingredients above.
3. Top the dip with extra cheese and tajin and serve with your favorite chips!

You can add jalapeño or hot sauce to the dip to give it a spicy kick. You can also add cilantro but I’m one of those people who thinks cilantro tastes like soap so I added green onions to the top of my dip. You can make this dip hot by bringing all the ingredients together on the stove or just serve it cold for a refreshing bite! Let me know if you make it and enjoy!

Let’s make Tomatokeftedes! ✨🍅

I’m still riding the high of our Greek honeymoon earlier this month and have been missing the amazing food we had. Fortunately, the cooking class we went to sent us home with the recipes we learned to make that day and this is my version of Tomatokeftedes, or fried tomato fritters, that I adapted using produce from local farms found in @dierbergs Homegrown section. Dierbergs has a wide variety of local produce that is picked, packed, and delivered to stores within 24 hours so you know it is fresh!

Ingredients:
• 2 tomatoes, chopped
• 1 zucchini, grated
• 2 green onions, chopped
• 2 tablespoons dill
• 2 tablespoons parsley
• ½ cup flour (I used rice flour for gluten-free)
• Salt and pepper to taste
• Oil for frying (I used avocado oil)
• Lemon (optional)

Instructions:
• Squeeze and drain as much liquid from the tomatoes and zucchini as possible
• Combine tomato, zucchini, green onion, dill, parsley, flour, salt, and pepper
• Heat oil on medium-high heat
• Drop spoonfuls of tomato mixture into the oil
• Fry each spoonful for 2-3 minutes per side until golden brown
• Carefully remove balls to a cooling rack or plate with paper towels
• (Optional) Sprinkle finishing salt and squeeze lemon • juice over fritters
• Serve with tzatziki or other condiment of your choice

I hope you enjoy this recipe and remember to support your local farmers at Dierbergs!

Slow Cooker Hatch Chile Chili 🌶️🍠

This is one of my go-to recipes when I need a hearty bowl of something warm and tasty! It is so easy to put everything in a slow cooker and you can tailor the recipe however you need. It is currently hatch chile season at @dierbergs so head on over there to pick up some hatch chiles to kick your chili up a notch!

Ingredients:
2 lbs cooked ground beef
1 large sweet potato, diced
1 onion, chopped
4 hatch chiles
28 oz. can diced fire roasted tomatoes
2 tablespoons tomato paste
2 cups, beef or chicken stock
2 tablespoons chili powder
1 tablespoon cumin
1 tablespoon paprika
¼ teaspoon red pepper
1 teaspoon salt
½ teaspoon black pepper

Instructions:
• Broil the hatch chiles for 5 minutes on each side. Put them on a plate and cover it in plastic wrap to help them steam. Peel off the skins, cut them open, and spoon out the seeds. Chop the chiles into bite-sized pieces.
• Combine all of the ingredients into a slower cooker.
• Cook on high for 3-4 hours or low for 6-8, until the sweet potatoes are tender.

Tips: If you are vegan or vegetarian, leave the beef out, substitute veggie stock, and add any other vegetables to the mix. Use the red pepper to increase or decrease the spice level to your preference. Remove the sweet potato if that’s not your thing, but I love adding it to my chili!

PEANUT BUTTER PUMPKIN DOG TREATS 🥜🎃🐾

Welcome to cooking with @carlielaughs and @stepheneatsstl in the Dierbergs School of Cooking kitchen! We’ve got a perfect fall treat you can make for your favorite pups. Be sure to stop by your local @dierbergs to pick up these simple ingredients to make some homemade treats!

Ingredients:
• 2.5 cups flour
• 2 eggs
• ½ cup canned pumpkin
• 2 tablespoons peanut butter
• ½ teaspoon salt
• ½ teaspoon cinnamon

Instructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350
2. Combine all of the ingredients in a bowl and mix together
3. Work the mixture with your hands until a dough starts to form
4. Roll the dough flat (approx ½ inch thick)
5. Cut out treats in your favorite shape and place on a baking sheet
6. Bake for 20-25 minutes until golden brown
7. Let the treats cool before giving to your dog

We hope your furry friends love them as much as our Barb and Bruce do! Tag us if you make these and let us know what you want to see us make next time 😉

PizzaCharity Review Ep. 2: @stepheneatsstl and I met up for a great meal at @pizzeoli 
If I had to choose a “Last Meal On Earth”, it would be Pizzeoli. 

How Does PizzaCharity Work? We donate one meal to charities fighting hunger for every 10 likes, comment, share, save and follow!

REVIEW TIME: 
🍗 Tallow Fried Wings - Insane Crunch, Super Tender Meat, Perfectly Seasoned Batter. The Sauce Flight about knocked me out with flavor 😂 Their Mayfair Dressing should come with an “Illegally Delicious” warning label. 

🍘 Arancini - Perfect blend of crunch from the panko on the outside and creamy from the Parmesan Saffron risotto on the inside. Major applause to Pizzeoli for serving six arancini balls per order since I feel like so many restaurants cheap out and serve you one arancini. 

💙 BlueNote Louie - My all time favorite pizza at Pizzeoli. If you have never had béchamel on pizza, you are missing out. That sauce pairs so well with the roasted chicken, Parmesan, mozzarella and rosemary and checked all the flavor boxes! However, the greatest quality of this pizza is the perfect contrast between the creamy blend of toppings and the crispy char of the wood fired crust. 

🍕The BetterBird - This was our final stop in Flavortown and wow did it not disappoint. The combination of their Bourbon Butter BBQ sauce, paired with Bacon + Chicken for the meats, Smoked Mozzarella + Smoked Gouda + Parmesan for the cheeses, and Red Onion + Green Onion for the veggies, achieved the perfect balance of flavors where no single flavor overpowered the other. 

As a former Neapolitan Pizzaiolo, I really appreciate the creative approach Pizzeoli takes to their pizza menu. So many times strict, Neapolitan traditions force restaurants to avoid exploring creative combinations of flavors that you wouldn’t expect to find on a pizza. Thank you Pizzeoli ❤️!
